<reference id="conbody" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>conbody</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>conbody</xmlelement> element
is the main body-level element for a concept. </shortdesc>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm><xmlelement>conbody</xmlelement></indexterm><indexterm>concept elements<indexterm><xmlelement>conbody</xmlelement></indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section id="conbodysection">Like the <xmlelement>body</xmlelement> element of a general
            <xmlelement>topic</xmlelement>, <xmlelement>conbody</xmlelement> allows paragraphs,
         lists, and other elements as well as sections and examples. However,
            <xmlelement>conbody</xmlelement> has a restriction that a
            <xmlelement>section</xmlelement> or an <xmlelement>example</xmlelement> can be followed
         only by other sections, examples, or <xmlelement>conbodydiv</xmlelement> elements that
         group sections and examples.</section>
